iv. The 2 sexes are affected in equal numbers (because the defective gene resides on one of the 22 autosomes (i.e. nonsex chromosomes). The exceptions to this rule are the sexlimited disorders such as breast \& ovarian cancers in females \& familial male precocious puberty in boys.

